{"id":48908,"title":"Acquired hypothyroidism due to iodine deficiency in an American child.","abstract":"Acquired hypothyroidism secondary to iodine deficiency is rarely reported in iodine-replete environments. The case of a 9-year-old patient with severe acquired hypothyroidism due to iodine deficiency is presented. His deficiency occurred because of a restrictive diet used to control eosinophilic esophagitis. Hypothyroidism and iodine deficiency were quickly corrected with a kelp supplement.","date":"2014-11-04","categories":"Endocrine System Diseases","split":"test","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25003378","annotations":[{"name":"Hypothyroidism","weight":0.643564,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hypothyroidism"},{"name":"Diet (nutrition)","weight":0.39426,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diet_(nutrition)"},{"name":"Child","weight":0.282633,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Child"},{"name":"United States","weight":0.160714,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States"},{"name":"Iodine","weight":0.102918,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iodine"},{"name":"Iodine deficiency","weight":0.0711346,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iodine_deficiency"},{"name":"Dietary supplement","weight":0.0670588,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dietary_supplement"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.0554043,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Esophagitis","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Esophagitis"},{"name":"Eosinophilic","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eosinophilic"},{"name":"Eosinophilic esophagitis","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eosinophilic_esophagitis"},{"name":"Kelp","weight":0.0274275,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kelp"},{"name":"Secondary education","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"htt